a gets restored at the end of test methods.\n\nNow checking the RST structure, I'm seeing 4 h2 headings in the source document that map to the 4 sections in the knowledge file. The 環境構築 section is quite substantial since it consolidates multiple h3 subsections like the backup schema creation and component configuration setup.\n\nLooking at the content breakdown, there's a configuration table with settings and examples, followed by log output configuration sections with property files. The plain text for this entire 環境構築 section exceeds 2000 characters and contains h3 subsections, but the knowledge file merges everything into s4 without splitting them out separately. This appears to be a V3 issue that should be flagged.\n\nNow checking the hints completeness for class names—I can see `MasterDataRestorer` and `NopLogWriter` are captured, but `BasicLoggerFactory` and `StandardOutputLogWriter` are missing from the hints. I've confirmed that `BasicLoggerFactory` and `StandardOutputLogWriter` are indeed missing from the hints. Now let me compile the full set of findings: there's a minor V3 issue where the 環境構築 section in s4 exceeds 2000 characters with multiple h3 subsections but isn't split into separate knowledge entries, and a minor V4 issue with those two missing class names from the hints.\n\nLooking back at the V1 rule more carefully, I'm noticing the source explicitly warns that master data changes during tests can cause subsequent test classes to fail, but the knowledge file doesn't capture this important consequence—it only implies it through the feature's purpose description.\n\nHowever, this is really just context explaining why the feature exists rather than decision-critical information, so I'll leave it as is.\n\nI've identified two minor issues: V3 has an oversized 環境構築 section that should be split into separate knowledge entries, and V4 is missing some PascalCase class names in the hints. No critical problems overall.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"